meanings.definition: To jump higher or farther than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The rabbit outjumps the turtle in the race.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outjumps his competitors in the long jump event.
meanings.sent3: The kangaroo outjumps the squirrel in a playful hopping contest.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm outjumps her fear when she takes the leap.
meanings.sent5: The superhero outjumps the building in a single bound.

meanings.sent1: The frog outjumps all other creatures in the pond.
meanings.sent2: The grasshopper outjumps its predators to escape danger.
meanings.sent3: The energetic puppy outjumps its own shadow in excitement.
meanings.sent4: His determination outjumps any obstacles in his path.
meanings.sent5: The champion outjumps the world record with an incredible leap.
